Titolo: Perseus and Andromeda (video game)

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Perseus and Andromeda is a text adventure video game released in  1983 by Digital Fantasia on the Mysterious Adventures label. It was available for the ZX Spectrum, Atari 8-bit, Acorn Electron, BBC Micro, Commodore 64, Dragon 32/64, and Oric-1.
Perseus and Andromeda was written by Brian Howarth in Scott Adams database. The story is an adaptation of the Greek myth of Perseus and includes characters and artifacts such as the winged sandals, Pegasus, the harpies and Medusa. The objective is to save Andromeda from the sea-monster Ceto.